FBIS3-3110 "drchi052_b_94003" FBIS-CHI-94-052 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Mar 1994 United States & Canada U.S. Extends Nuclear Test Moratorium OW1503223894 Beijing XINHUA in English 2125 GMT 15 Mar 94 OW1503223894 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Washington, March 15 (XINHUA) -- The United States announced today that it would extend for one more year its moratorium on nuclear testing when it expires in September. President Bill Clinton notified congressional leaders of the extension on Monday [14 March]. Any resumption of nuclear weapons testing would have to be approved by Congress. "The President will decide next year whether to extend the moratorium beyond September 1995," White House Spokeswoman Dee Dee Myers said. The U.S. Congress has set a September 1996 target for an end to nuclear tests.
